<p style="text-align:left; text-indent: -0.5in; margin-left: 0.5in"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 12pt">§294.  Standard deduction</span></span></p>
<p style="text-align:left"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 12pt"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>A.  A standard deduction shall be allowed in determining a taxpayer's tax liability
pursuant to this Part.  Taxpayers are required to use the same filing status on their return
required to be filed under this Part as they used on their federal income tax return.  For tax
year 2025, the amount of the standard deduction shall be as follows:</span></span></p>
<p style="text-align:left"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 12pt"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>(1)  Single Individual and Married-Separate<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>$12,500.00</span></span></p>
<p style="text-align:left; text-indent: -4in; margin-left: 4in"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 12pt"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>(2)  Married-Joint Return, a Qualified Surviving <span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>200% of the dollar amount</span></span></p>
<p style="text-align:left; text-indent: -4in; margin-left: 4in"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 12pt"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Spouse, and Head of Household<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>provided for Single Individuals</span></span></p>
<p style="text-align:left"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 12pt"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>B.  Beginning January 1, 2026, and thereafter, the amount of the standard deduction
provided in Subsection A of this Section shall be adjusted annually by an amount calculated
by multiplying the amount of the prior year's standard deduction by the percentage increase
in the Consumer Price Index United States city average for all urban consumers (CPI-U), as
reported by the United States Department of Labor, Bureau of Labor Statistics, or its
successor, for the previous calendar year.</span></span></p>
<p style="text-align:left"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 12pt"><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Acts 1980, No. 316, §1.  Acts 1983, 2nd Ex. Sess., No. 1, §1, eff. Dec. 19, 1983; Acts
2024, 3rd Ex. Sess., No. 11, §2, eff. Dec. 4, 2024.</span></span></p>
